officialTitle: Gonadotropin Releasing Hormone Agonist for Luteal Phase Support in Long Gonadotropin Releasing Hormone Agonist Protocol Cycles
inclusionCriteria:
* Women subjected to ICSI through controlled ovarian hyperstimulation (COH) with pituitary downregulation by GnRHa.
* Must be FEMALE
* Must have minimum age of 20 Years
* Must have maximum age of 38 Years
exclusionCriteria:
* Moderate or severe endometriosis.
* Hydrosalpinx.
* Uterine abnormalities.
* Myoma.
* Previous uterine surgery.
